PORT HARCOURT – Dr Chinyere Igwe, a staunch supporter of former Vice President Atiku Abubakar, presidential candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party, has been arrested with an unspecified amount of foreign currencies. Igwe, who represents Port Harcourt Federal Constituency 2, in the House of Representatives, was arrested on Friday morning along Aba Road in Port Harcourt. Spokesperson of the Rivers State Police Command, Grace Iringe-Koko, who confirmed the arrest to our correspondent said, “A statement on it will be released soon. Details later… •The PUNCH